The paper deals with constructing a non-interactive key exchange protocol using isogenies on elliptic curves, which is a topic closely related to cryptography and information theory (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the construction of a cryptographic invariant map, which is a new primitive in cryptography and could be of interest to researchers in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves mathematical algorithms and computations, which could be relevant to researchers in discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of the proposed protocol, which could be of interest to researchers in cybersecurity (cs.CY).
